What the contract does:
The contract generates random nos.(supposedly) and asks us to guess those nos.
The vulnerability:
The value of the random nos. generated by it were completely dependent on the block on which the transsaction was happening. If someone is able to run their attack on the same block, they can also guess the supposedly random no.
How I exploited it:
I  exploited it by using the same code as the contract and doing the calculations on the same block.
Prevention:
Solidity doesn't yet have a method by which it can generate completely random nos. so if the random nos. aren't generated by using external help like Oracle, they can be guessed by the attacker by using the same code as in the vulnerable contract.
